Paper: hep-th/0005018

Date: 2000-05-02

Title: Zero modes in finite range magnetic fields

Authors: C. Adam, B. Muratori, C. Nash

Comments: 5 pages, Latex, no figures

Journal-ref: Mod.Phys.Lett. A15 (2000) 1577-1582

We find a class of Fermion zero modes of Abelian Dirac operators in threedimensional Euclidean space where the gauge potentials and the related magneticfields are nonzero only in a finite space region.